observations.recommendation:
We recommended that the Management:


Ensure that all identified development projects embodied in the Annual Investment Program are supported with concrete plans and designs, without any hindering issues and procurement-and-implementation-ready, including conduct of detailed engineering for infrastructure projects, in order to complete them within the target completion date to maximize the benefit for its intended beneficiaries;



Prepare a holistic and comprehensive but realistic catch-up plan, after conducting proper monitoring and follow-up activities, to expedite the project implementation of ppas funded especially from prior years’ appropriation, which are still at the agency pipeline, to reduce backlogs;

Review the balances of the continuing appropriations as part of the annual budget preparation process and consider the need for reprogramming of the ppas from prior years’ appropriations, where necessary, after determination of a more relevant and responsive and procurement-and-implementation-ready projects that may be included under the 20% Development Fund of the Municipality in adherence with applicable laws, rules and regulations; and

Require a certification from the Engineering Office that the detailed engineering surveys and designs have been conducted for infrastructure projects to ensure readiness of the procurement at hand, pursuant to Item 5 of Annex A of the revised IRR of RA 9184.
